        <abstract> 
<p>Thanks AB for his paper on the Norwegian flora ["Forsög til en Theori om Invandringen af Norges Flora", <hi rend="italic">Nyt Mag. Naturvidensk.</hi> 21 (1876): 279–362]. Appears to CD to be the most important contribution towards understanding the present distribution of plants since Edward Forbes’s essay on the effects of the glacial period ["On the connexion between the distribution of existing fauna and flora of the British Isles and the geological changes which have affected their area", <hi rend="italic">Mem. Geol. Surv. Engl. &amp; Wales</hi> 1 (1846): 336–432].</p> 
        </abstract>
